				<h1 class="page-header">Forum Owner Rotation?</h1>
				<h2 style="color:green">Goal:</h2> 
				<ul class="howthisworkslist">
					<li>Actively track and answer all StackOverflow and MSDN Azure Storage questions.</li>
					<li>Ensure that no question goes unanswered for more than <strong style="color:red">3 days</strong>.</li>
					<li>XFE and XClient Engineers and PMs are eligible for forum owner rotation. Contact micurd if you’d like to be included in the rotation</li>
					<li>Forum owner shifts are weekly.</li>
					<li>The forum owner rotation can be found <a href="/forumowner">here</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<h1 class="page-header">Stack Overflow Setup</h1>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<ul>
						<li>Go to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/signup">https://stackoverflow.com/users/signup</a></li>
						<li>Choose to create your login on StackExchange.</li>
						<li>As your Display Name, enter "<your real name> - MSFT“</li>
						<li>As your e-mail address, enter your work email address or another address that you use for work.</li>
						<li>You will receive an email to confirm your address. After you get this, follow the link and then edit your profile.</li>
						<li>Correct your Display Name to the same as step 3.</li>
						<li>As your Real Name, enter your real name, first and last.</li>
						<li>Website is optional (you could put in your LinkedIn url or use the Storage blog <a href="http://blogs.msdn.com/b/windowsazurestorage/">http://blogs.msdn.com/b/windowsazurestorage/</a>)</li>
						<li>As your Location, enter Redmond, WA</li>
						<li>No need to enter your birthday.</li>
						<li>In the "About Me" section, mention that you are part of the Azure Storage Engineering team</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<img class="howthisworksimg" src = "/images/stackoverflowsetup.png">
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<h1 class="page-header">MSDN Setup</h1>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<ul>
						<li>Go to: <a href="http://social.microsoft.com/Forums/en-US/categories">http://social.microsoft.com/Forums/en-US/categories</a></li>   
						<li>Click the “Sign in” link  at the top right of the page</li> 
						<li>If you do not have a Windows Live ID you will need to create one</li> 
						<li>Once you have signed in with a valid Live ID you will need to fill out your Social profile</li> 
						<li>Once you have completed and saved your profile, you will need to associate your Live ID and profile to your Microsoft network credentials at the following URL: <a href="http://social.msdn.microsoft.com/profile/u/associate/microsoft/">http://social.msdn.microsoft.com/profile/u/associate/microsoft/</a></li>  
						<li>This will automatically put a “(MSFT)” indicator after your display name so customers can always see that you work for Microsoft.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<img class="howthisworksimg" src="/images/msdnsetup.png">
				</div>
